.TH "mc7_calc_size" 9 "mc7_calc_size" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mc7_calc_size \- calculate MC7 memory size
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" mc7_calc_size
.BI "(u32 cfg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cfg" 12
the MC7 configuration

Calculates the size of an MC7 memory in bytes from the value of its
configuration register.
